*** NickServ Help ***
NickServ allows you to "register" a nickname and
prevent others from using it. The following commands
allow for registration and maintenance of nicknames;
to use them, type: /ns COMMAND
 
Command        Description
 
ACC        - View current access of a nickname
ACCESS     - Modify the list of authorized addresses
DROP       - Cancel the registration of a nickname
GHOST      - Terminates a "ghost" IRC session using your nick
IDENTIFY   - Identify yourself with your password
INFO       - Display information on a registered nickname
LISTCHANS  - Display channels you have access to
RECOVER    - Regain your nickname if someone else is using it
REGISTER   - Register a nickname
RELEASE    - Release services custody on a nickname
RESETPASS  - Resets your password through a verification code
SET        - Set various nickname options
 
For more information on a specific command,
type: /ns HELP command
 
Note: This service is intended to provide a way for IRC
users to ensure their identity is not compromised. It is
NOT intended to facilitate "stealing" of nicknames or
other malicious actions. Abuse of NickServ will result in,
at minimum, loss of the abused nickname(s) and channels
registered by them.
 
Type /join #IRCHelp for more information.
*** End of Help ***